
[1]divest

   DIVEST, v.t. [L. It is the same word as devest, but the latter is
   appropriately used as a technical term in law.]

   1. To strip of clothes, arms or equipage; opposed to invest.

   2. To deprive; as, to divest one of his rights or privileges; to divest
   one of title or property.

   3. To deprive or strip of any thing that covers , surrounds or attends;
   as, to divest one of his glory; to divest a subject of deceptive
   appearances, or false ornaments.
